## üî¨ Scientific Basis & Studies  

- **Mycoremediation** is the use of fungi to remove pollutants.
  - Stamets, P. (2005). *Mycelium Running: How Mushrooms Can Help Save the World*.
- *Pleurotus ostreatus* has been proven to degrade hydrocarbons, CO, and formaldehyde.
- Fungi emit beneficial spores that colonize damaged ecosystems.
- Towers emulate **passive evaporative cooling towers** and **natural filter beds**.

> Citation: Sharma, A. et al. (2018). Biodegradation of Air Pollutants Using Fungal Systems. *Ecological Engineering Journal*.

